However, the number of people contracting HIV in this way has virtually decreased in its entirety, Chinese health authorities declared at a congress held in the province of Yunnan.
Each year, the number of people living with HIV and AIDS in China increases about 100,000 people.
Sexual HIV transmission is a serious problem in the LGTB community in China.
Homosexuality was decriminalized in China in 1997, but the LGTB collective suffers great discrimination.
Due to the country’s conservative values, studies have calculated that between 70% and 90% of men who have sex with other men will end up marrying women.
Many of the transmissions of diseases are due to failure to use adequate protection in these relationships.
Since 2003, the Chinese government has pledged universal access to HIV drugs as part of an attempt to address the problem.
